HEADWORD: crepitant
<hw>crep"i*tant</hw> <pr>(kr?p"?-t<it>a</it>nt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[See <er>Crepitate</er>.]</ety> <def>Having a crackling sound;
crackling; rattling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Crepitant rale</b></col> <fld>(Med.)</fld>, <cd>a
peculiar crackling sound audible with inspiration in pneumonia and other
lung disease.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

